y, this only yields synthesis sparsity w.r.t. the dual\nframe, about which often only little is known. But our theory yields synthesis\nsparsity w.r.t. the well-understood primal frame.\n  In particular, our theory applies to $\\alpha$-modulation spaces and inhom.\nBesov spaces. It also applies to shearlet frames, as we show in a companion\npaper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Dec 2016 23:45:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-30"}
